<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,595,226,252]" box="[151,595,226,252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,595,226,252]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,595,226,252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Family 
<taxonomicName authority="Hilton, 1942" authorityName="Hilton" authorityYear="1942" box="[246,595,226,252]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Callipallenidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Callipallenidae Hilton, 
<number box="[537,595,226,252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1942.0">1942</number>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,301,527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
The attribution of this genus to the family 
<taxonomicName box="[646,826,301,327]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Callipallenidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Callipallenidae</taxonomicName>
, as done by 
<bibRefCitation author="Child" box="[970,1121,301,327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" refString="Child, C. A. (1982) Deep-Sea Pycnogonida from the North and South Atlantic Basins. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 349, 54 pp." type="book" year="1982">
Child (
<number box="[1051,1112,301,327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Stock" box="[1178,1332,301,327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" refString="Stock, J. H. (1994) Indo-West Pacific Pycnogonida collected by some major oceanographic expeditions. Beaufortia, 44 (3), 17 - 77." type="journal article" year="1994">
Stock (
<number box="[1260,1323,301,327]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, must be regarded as somewhat speculative; for example, no other callipallenid genus lacks chelifores. Indeed, Barnard (locc. cit.) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Arnaud" box="[333,663,381,407]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" refString="Arnaud, F. &amp; Bamber, R. N. (1987) The Biology of Pycnogonida. Advances in Marine Biology, 24, 1 - 96. Academic Press, Inc." type="journal article" year="1987">
Arnaud and Bamber (
<number box="[593,654,381,407]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
regarded its familial attribution as 
<emphasis box="[1085,1250,381,406]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">incertae sedis</emphasis>
. There are perhaps as many grounds for placing the genus within the 
<taxonomicName box="[801,970,421,447]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Ammotheidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ammotheidae</taxonomicName>
, although the placement and conformation of the palp in the new species (see below) is not consistent for that family. The 
<taxonomicName box="[1237,1403,461,487]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Ammotheidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ammotheidae</taxonomicName>
is polyphyletic (as is the 
<taxonomicName box="[416,595,501,527]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Callipallenidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Callipallenidae</taxonomicName>
) and currently in a state of revision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
